author: Nicola Agius
title: Robbie Fowler eliminated from The Jump 2017 as he admits: 'The other celebs are better than me'
text:
Robbie Fowler has been eliminated from The Jump 2017 . 
He is the third celebrity to lose his place in the competition since it started last month. 
Although the former footballer admitted he wish he had performed better, he insisted there were no hard feelings during his exit chat with Davina McCall. 
"I have absolutely loved this, it’s been a wonderful experience," he said. "I wish I’d stayed a bit longer but look these guys are all fantastic and you know what they’re all much better than me so they all deserve to be here." Robbie Fowler has been eliminated from The Jump 2017 (Photo: Channel 4) 
After losing the Skeleton head to head race, Robbie was forced to head to the top of The Jump to fight to stay in the competition against Louis Smith and Amy Willerton. Read More The Jump fans suspicious as injured Bradley Wiggins competes AFTER pulling out - but there's an explanation 
Unfortunately for the football star, following a fall in training, he crashed on the outrun. Although the former footballer admitted he wish he had performed better, he insisted there were no hard feelings during his exit chat with Davina McCall (Photo: Channel 4) 
Luckily, he didn't suffer any injuries but the slip-up meant he received a No Jump. 
At the end of the show, the three remaining jumpers Lydia Bright, Emma Parker-Bowles and Kadeena Cox just needed to successfully jump to keep their place in the competition due to Robbie's earlier performance. 
Emma was up first with a good jump in challenging and foggy conditions, landing 10.93m. Robbie is the third celeb to be eliminated (Photo: PA) 
Lydia was up next with her first appearance on the ski jump, she looked nervous but pulled it off with a distance of 11.50m. 
Kadeena then managed to also land safely falling just after the end line meaning her jump of 13.48m counted, knocking Robbie out of the competition. 
The Jump returns next Sunday at 7:30pm on Channel 4 when the remaining competitors will take on Ski Cross. Like us on Facebook
